  "title": "Project Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Project management skills such as time management and project scheduling</li><li>Coordinating subcontractors & building management to ensure optimal level of client satisfaction and administer everyday operation for projects</li><li>Monitoring progress and identifying critical activities to expedite smooth progress of works on site to meet targets.</li><li>Ensure that work are executed in accordance with approved plans/drawings, contract specifications and regulatory requirements.</li><li>Communicates effectively with design & project teams, consultants and subcontractors to identify needs and evaluate alternative Project solutions.</li><li>Any other ad hoc duties</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Candidate must processes at least Nitec/Diploma in design or equivalent</li><li>At least 3 years of relevant industry experience </li><li>Able to identify specialist drawing/architectural/MEP details</li><li>Able to multitask and manage time efficiently</li><li>Strong communication skills, as well as the ability to visualise issues and effectively communicate with others.</li></ul>",
